references:
Current experiment presents illustration of application of proposed algorithms to multipartite entity resolution problem. Experiment settings and results are displayed in table 5. We have collected list of 2610 highly cited researcher names from (http://www.webometrics.info/en/node/58) and selected subset of size N of their names. Next, we created three identical datasets D1subscript𝐷1D_{1}, D2subscript𝐷2D_{2}, and D3subscript𝐷3D_{3}. Column e denotes error: probability under which random letter of any item in D1subscript𝐷1D_{1} or D2subscript𝐷2D_{2} would be changed to random letter. Part of distorted dataset is shown in table 4. We have generated input matrix as per formulation 3, using trigram similarity as similarity function, and performed greedy search as in algorithm 1, and then improved it using VLSN with greedy start (alg. 2).
